Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount), then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the pan, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with salt and pepper. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once your pan is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Mix in the @crème fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with pepper. Stir through three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Stir the cooked pasta through your creamy sauce along with half the cooked green veg. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Share the creamy pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining cooked green veg.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!